  "prompt": "How can I overcome a mobile phone addiction?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to overcome mobile phone addiction:\n\n1. Track and limit screen time\n- Use built-in phone tracking apps\n- Set daily time limits for phone usage\n- Turn off unnecessary notifications\n\n2. Create phone-free zones and times\n- No phones during meals\n- Keep phone out of bedroom\n- Disable phone during work/study hours\n\n3. Practice mindful usage\n- Be intentional about phone use\n- Ask yourself why you're picking up the phone\n- Set specific purposes for phone interactions\n\n4. Find alternative activities\n- Read books\n- Exercise\n- Engage in hobbies\n- Spend time with people face-to-face\n\n5. Use technological tools\n- Install apps that block distracting websites\n- Use grayscale mode to make phone less appealing\n- Keep phone in another room while working\n\n6. Gradually reduce usage\n- Start with small, achievable reduction goals\n- Replace phone time with productive activities\n- Be patient with yourself\n\n7. Digital detox strategies\n- Take periodic breaks from your phone\n- Have phone-free days\n- Go on tech-free vacations\n\n8. Address underlying issues\n- Understand what drives excessive phone use\n- Consider counseling if addiction is severe\n- Practice stress management techniques\n\nConsistency and self-awareness are key to overcoming mobile phone addiction.",
